A swarm of five guards come storming out of the palace after you.  You fight valiantly and desperately against overwhelming odds.	五名衛兵蜂擁而出，從宮殿追殺過來。你在絕對劣勢下奮力抵抗，殊死一戰。
Suddenly, the Djinni cries "No!  Iblis is loose!"  You and the guards turn as you hear a rumbling and crashing from inside the Palace.	突然，精靈大喊：「不！伊布利斯掙脫了！」你和衛兵們轉頭，聽見宮殿內傳來轟隆巨響。
Hey, this guy knows Magic.	嘿，這傢伙懂魔法。
     Guards, To me!     	     衛兵，到我身邊來！
What is going on?  Guards!  The gate!!	發生什麼事了？衛兵！大門！！
Go get him, Elija-One!  I'll watch you make short work of this hero.	去抓他，伊萊賈一號！我倒要看看你怎麼三兩下解決這位英雄。
Why, I oughta....!	哼，我真該……！
I would if I could see ya!!	要是我看得到你，我早就動手了！！
What is going on down there?	下面發生什麼事了？
You have no need to bust down doors up here, but you better get moving.	你不需要在這裡破門而入，但你最好快點行動。
Khaveen cries out in pain and the guard summons other guards who quickly subdue you.  Khaveen makes certain that you will never bother him again.	哈維因痛得大叫，衛兵隨即召來其他人手迅速將你制伏。哈維因確保你再也不能來煩他。
Your attack awakens Khaveen who alerts the guards in the other room.  You are quickly overwhelmed.  It would be best if you don't announce your presence when attempting to be a burglar.	你的攻擊驚醒了哈維因，他立刻示警隔壁房間的衛兵。你很快就被制伏了。當小偷時，最好別讓人察覺你的存在。
What looked at first like a woman sleeping is actually a man with a beard.	乍看像是熟睡的女子，其實是個蓄鬍的男人。
Get closer to the cabinet.	靠近櫃子一點。
Pity.  You don't have any oil.	可惜，你沒有油。
As you move towards Khaveen, a board squeaks and Khaveen turns to look at you.  Your weapon can't stop him from starting to shout.  You are quickly overwhelmed and dragged off to the dungeon, but at least you have some satisfaction knowing Khaveen will no longer trouble Raseir.	你朝哈維因靠近時，地板發出嘎吱聲，哈維因轉頭看向你。你的武器無法阻止他放聲大喊。你很快就被制伏，並被拖進地牢，但至少你能安慰自己，哈維因再也不能為害拉希爾了。
You are already hiding as well as you can.	你已經盡力躲藏了。
You're already standing up.	你已經站起來了。
As you hold the bird in your hand, for a moment you wonder, "Is this the stuff dreams are made of?"  You decide:  "Nah," and put it away.	你手握著這隻鳥，一瞬間心想：「這就是夢想成真的感覺嗎？」你打消念頭：「算了吧。」便將它收了起來。
Screeack	嘎吱
As you and the man look at each other, you realize just whose house this is.   Khaveen calls for his guards, and you are quickly overwhelmed. Khaveen then takes a sword and personally makes certain you'll never steal again.	你和那名男子四目相對，這才驚覺這是誰的宅邸。哈維因叫來衛兵，你很快就被制伏。哈維因隨即拔劍，親自確保你再也無法偷竊。
The Guards from the other room calmly arrest you and place you in prison for a short, but unpleasant time.  Khaveen is not kind to those that break into his house and use magic against him, but you do not live to tell about it.	隔壁房間的衛兵冷靜地將你逮捕，關進監牢度過一段短暫卻難受的時光。哈維因對闖入他家並對他施法的人絕不留情，但你活不下來訴說這段經歷。
The guard quickly calls in other guards, and you are overwhelmed.  Khaveen then takes a sword and personally makes certain you'll never steal again.  The last thing you see is the smile on Khaveen's face.	衛兵迅速召來其他人手，你被制伏了。哈維因隨即拔劍，親自確保你再也無法偷竊。你看見的最後一幕，是哈維因臉上的微笑。
The cabinet door is closed.	櫃門是關著的。
Your spell has no effect after passing through the bed's veils.	你的法術穿過床幔後便失去效力。
You can't Fetch the cabinet.	你無法「取得」這個櫃子。
You already have the statue of the bird.	你已經拿到鳥形雕像了。
Creeeak!	嘎吱！
You find you cannot move. The man before you has a low, pleasant voice, and eyes like a snake.	你發現自己動彈不得。眼前的男子聲音低沉悅耳，眼神卻如蛇一般。
%s, I am your friend.	%s，我是你的朋友。
Trust in your friend, and Obey me.	相信你的朋友，聽從我。
%s, you know me.  I am your friend, Ad Avis, who helped you escape from the dungeons of Raseir.	%s，你認識我。我是你的朋友，阿德·阿維斯，曾幫你逃出拉希爾的地牢。
Together we seek to aid our friend, Emir Arus.  I was his trusted Vizier, remember?	我們一起尋求幫助我們的朋友，埃米爾阿魯斯。我曾是他信任的維齊爾，記得嗎？
We must journey to the Forbidden City, and recover the magic item that will break the spell upon the Emir.	我們必須前往禁城，取回能解除埃米爾身上詛咒的魔法物品。
We NEED to get the statue of Iblis!	我們一定要拿到伊布利斯的雕像！
You remember the statue of Iblis, don't you?  It has remarkable powers, and can break any spell it touches.	你記得伊布利斯的雕像吧？它擁有驚人的力量，能解除任何它碰觸到的法術。
Together you will save the Emir.  You and Ad Avis will get the statue of Iblis.	你們將一起拯救埃米爾。你和阿德·阿維斯會去取得伊布利斯的雕像。
You see an open doorway.	你看見一扇敞開的門口。
The door is securely barred from the inside.	這扇門從裡面牢牢閂上了。
You see an open door.	你看見一扇敞開的門。
There is an uninteresting-looking door here.	這裡有一扇不起眼的門。
The Slave Woman glares at you.	那名女奴瞪著你。
You're already wearing them.	你已經戴上了。
You put on the Ali Fakir Genuine X-Ray Glasses.	你戴上了阿里·法基爾正宗透視眼鏡。
You take them off and put them away.	你把它們摘下並收好。
As you start, you see fear in the Slave Woman's eyes.	你才剛開始，就看見女奴眼中閃過恐懼。
Guards quickly burst into the room.  They drag you off to prison and Khaveen personally oversees your stay.  It is not long.	衛兵迅速衝進房間，將你拖進監牢，哈維因親自監管你的牢獄生活。不會太久。
You exchange clothes with Zayishah since you no longer have any spare ones.  You don't look very Sheik in her veil, but it's a nice fit.  Suddenly the guards break in and drag you off to the Harem.  In two weeks, you are married to Khaveen, and you both live happily ever after.	你和札伊莎交換衣服，因為你已經沒有備用衣物了。戴著她的面紗，你看起來不太有型，不過倒是挺合身的。突然衛兵闖了進來，把你拖進後宮。兩週後，你嫁給了哈維因，從此過著幸福快樂的日子。
I wish to disguise myself as you and leave with your Visa, so please, let me exchange clothes with you.	我想偽裝成你，用你的通行證離開，所以請讓我和你交換衣服。
You Discover you have no Visa, so you offer her your Master's Card.  She Sears you with her gaze, then beats you to a pulp with a Macy and takes your money.  You are unable to Ward off the blows and are soon J. C. Penniless.	你發現自己沒有 Visa，只好遞給她 Master's Card。她用眼神死盯著你，接著抄起一根 Macy 棍棒把你打得半死，還搶走你的錢。你完全無法招架，很快就變得一文不名。
Please, Hero, your Visa.  There isn't much time.	拜託了，英雄，你的通行證呢？時間不多了。
Please, in order to leave the city I need one more thing, although it will be dangerous for you.  I must have your Visa.	拜託，要離開這座城市，我還需要一樣東西，雖然這對你來說很危險。我必須拿到你的通行證。
If you need a place of safety in the Palace sometime, the Harem will welcome you for the aid you gave my mistress.  I shall tie a veil from the battlements at night to guide you.	如果你日後在宮殿裡需要一處安全的地方，後宮會因為你曾幫助我家小姐而歡迎你。我會在夜裡從城垛上垂下一條面紗為你引路。
You are met outside by several guards, who cheerfully drag you away to the dungeons of Raseir.	你一出去就被幾名衛兵攔住，他們興高采烈地把你拖進拉希爾的地牢。
I must hurry before the Eunuchs discover I am gone.  Khaveen will have the city searched.  Please, may I have your Visa?	我必須在太監們發現我不見之前趕緊行動。哈維因會派人搜遍全城。拜託，能把你的通行證給我嗎？
Please, hero, we must hurry.  The guards will be searching for me soon.  I need your clothes.	拜託了，英雄，我們得快點。衛兵很快就會來搜查我。我需要你的衣服。
Suddenly, the guards walk in and grab all of you, just as Zayishah had warned.  Zayishah is returned to the Harem.   You are taken to the dungeon where Khaveen is waiting for you.	突然，衛兵闖了進來，把你們全部抓住，正如札伊莎所警告的那樣。札伊莎被送回後宮，你則被帶到地牢，哈維因正在那裡等著你。
The Eunuchs watch the women to make sure they cannot leave the Harem.	太監們看守著這些女子，確保她們無法離開後宮。
No man is allowed in the Harem.  The women there knows how to keep secrets.	後宮不許男子進入。裡頭的女子都懂得保守秘密。
There are many who resent Ad Avis and Khaveen, and wish to restore the city.	有許多人痛恨阿德·阿維斯和哈維因，希望能光復這座城市。
Khaveen.	哈維因。
The Sultan (May-he-reign-for ever) will care for Zayishah in Shapeir, if she can but get there.	蘇丹（願他萬歲萬萬歲）會在夏皮爾照顧札伊莎，只要她能平安抵達。
There is one Katta left in the city.  He is with the underground.	城裡還剩下一名卡塔族。他和地下組織在一起。
My father is Ali Al-Din Hasan.  He is the Emir of this city, at least in name, but he has no control over anything, not even in the Palace.  He is but a puppet for Khaveen and Ad Avis.	我父親是阿里·阿丁·哈山。他名義上是這座城市的埃米爾，但實際上什麼都管不了，就連在宮殿裡也一樣。他不過是哈維因和阿德·阿維斯的傀儡。
In your clothes, I can leave the city.  I have special letters of envoy signed by Khaveen.  I need only your Visa to be free.	穿上你的衣服，我就能離開這座城市。我有哈維因親筆簽署的特使信函。我只需要你的通行證就能重獲自由。
I am the Emir's Daughter, Zayishah.	我是埃米爾之女，札伊莎。
I fear and hate him more than Khaveen.  It is he who destroyed my Uncle Arus and made Raseir the terrible place it now is.  Ad Avis was my uncle's Vizier.  There are only two passions to Ad Avis: complete Power, and complete Control.  He will stop at nothing to gain those.	我對他的畏懼和憎恨甚至超過哈維因。是他毀了我的叔叔阿魯斯，把拉希爾變成如今這副可怕的模樣。阿德·阿維斯曾是我叔叔的維齊爾。他一心只追求兩件事：絕對的權力，以及絕對的控制。為了得到這些，他不擇手段。
All the women must stay there now, hiding their faces behind veils. Did you know it is forbidden for a man to speak to a woman unless she is his mother, daughter, or wife?  It is all Ad Avis's doing.  He must really hate women.	現在所有女子都得留在那裡，用面紗遮住臉。你知道嗎，男子除非對象是自己的母親、女兒或妻子，否則不准和女子說話？這一切都是阿德·阿維斯搞出來的。他一定很痛恨女人。
I do not know what magic Ad Avis has, but it is clear he is a Wizard.  You must not get near him unless you are protected against spells.	我不知道阿德·阿維斯擁有什麼樣的魔法，但他顯然是個巫師。除非你有防護法術的能力，否則絕不能靠近他。
The Palace is filled with guards and all women must stay in the Harem.	宮殿裡到處都是衛兵，所有女子都必須待在後宮。
I know how to survive in the desert, it is my home.  Before Ad Avis took over the city, I roamed it freely at will.  The caravan is but a day's ride ahead of me.  I will catch it easily.	我知道如何在沙漠中生存，那裡是我的家。在阿德·阿維斯佔領這座城市之前，我一直自由自在地在沙漠中遊蕩。商隊不過領先我一天的路程，我很容易就能追上。
The Fountain of the city dried up just after my Uncle Arus disappeared.	城裡的噴泉就在我叔叔阿魯斯失蹤後不久乾涸了。
The Katta cries out in pain, causing the guards to rush in.   They take you to a cell from which you can find no escape.	卡塔族痛得大叫，引來衛兵衝入。他們把你關進一間你找不到出路的牢房。
The cell is made from quarried rock, with massive iron bars and a huge gate.  Despite the heat outside, it is very cold in here.	這間牢房由開鑿的岩石建成，有著粗大的鐵欄和巨大的牢門。儘管外頭酷熱，這裡卻十分寒冷。
Thank you, for your kindness.  Now it's time to think about escaping.	謝謝你的好意。現在該想想怎麼逃出去了。
Thank you for offering, but it appears you are out of food.  But that's not the important issue here, it is time to think about escaping.	謝謝你的好意，不過你似乎已經沒有食物了。但這不是重點，現在該想想怎麼逃出去了。
The katta just stares suspiciously at you.	那名卡塔族只是狐疑地盯著你。
You hear the sounds of guards talking just outside the outer door.	你聽見外門外傳來衛兵交談的聲音。
The bars are made of thick iron.  Bending them would be out of the question.	這些欄杆是厚重的鐵製成的，想彎折它們根本不可能。
As you struggle with the astonishingly tough katta, the guards enter and separate you both, taking you to a cell from which you cannot escape.	你和這名出奇強壯的卡塔族纏鬥時，衛兵闖了進來把你們分開，將你關進一間無法逃脫的牢房。
The Katta raises his eyebrows in surprise, but then resumes his silent, suspicious stare.	卡塔族驚訝地挑起眉毛，但隨即又恢復沉默、狐疑的注視。
Thank you, my friend.	謝謝你，我的朋友。
That does not seem to be a sign the Katta recognizes, for he watches you with amusement.	這個手勢似乎不是卡塔族認得的，因為他只是饒富興味地看著你。
But he soon resumes his silent stare.	但他很快又恢復沉默的注視。
Which one?  There are many here, but none of them appear to be moveable.	哪一個？這裡有好多個，但看起來沒有一個能移動。
Nobody can stare down a katta.  After several seconds, you become bleary-eyed and turn away.	沒有人能瞪贏卡塔族。幾秒鐘後，你的雙眼開始模糊，只好轉開視線。
Your equipment is on the stone table.	你的裝備放在石桌上。
You had better leave quickly.  There's no time for a search now.	你最好快點離開。現在沒時間搜查了。
Good idea, but how?  Where?	好主意，但要怎麼做？在哪裡？
You look around and see a large stone whose mortar has been loosened.	你環顧四周，看見一塊灰泥已經鬆動的大石塊。
You find only the Katta and some straw.	你只找到那名卡塔族和一些稻草。
You find nothing but straw.	你只找到稻草，什麼都沒有。
You find a slightly rusty nail in a crack between the stones of the floor.	你在地板石縫間找到一根略帶鏽跡的釘子。
Remembering your Advanced Adventuring lessons, you set to work on the cell door lock, using the %s as a lockpick	想起你學過的進階冒險課程，你拿%s當開鎖工具，開始對付牢門的鎖
You can climb the bars easily, but that won't help you escape.	你可以輕鬆爬上欄杆，但這對逃脫毫無幫助。
The Katta isn't going anywhere he doesn't want to go.	卡塔族不會去任何他不想去的地方。
Go ahead.  The door's open.	去吧，門是開著的。
That could be hard to do while locked inside a jail cell.	被鎖在牢房裡，這件事恐怕很難辦到。
The katta watches you calmly with a mixture of interest and suspicion.	那名卡塔族平靜地看著你，眼神中混雜著興趣與懷疑。
A pin like that can only be seen by a friend, such is its magic.  It is Katta magic.  You must be very trusted by my people to gain such a thing.	這樣的別針只有朋友才看得見，這就是它的魔力所在。這是卡塔族的魔法。你一定深受我族人的信任，才能得到這樣的東西。
You find yourself crawling through a twisty passage for what seems like forever.  When it comes to a dead end, you force open another panel and find yourself in the streets of Raseir.	你發現自己在一條曲折的通道中爬行，彷彿沒有盡頭。走到死路時，你強行推開另一片嵌板，發現自己來到了拉希爾的街道上。
The entrance to the passageway should be here.....	通道的入口應該就在這裡……
The katta leads you through dark passages under the Palace to a secret exit into the Raseir streets.  Sharaf warns you that tomorrow night the Underground plans to attack the Palace and overthrow the Emir.	那名卡塔族領著你穿過宮殿底下的黑暗通道，來到通往拉希爾街道的秘密出口。沙拉夫警告你，地下組織計畫在明晚攻打宮殿、推翻埃米爾。
He shows you the passage that leads back towards the Blue Parrot Inn and reminds you to be wary of guards.  Then he bids you good luck and scurries off.	他為你指出通往藍鸚鵡旅店的通道，並提醒你要提防衛兵，接著祝你好運，匆匆離去。
You and Sharaf wander the passages beneath the Palace.  Without your equipment, you both perish in the darkness.	你和沙拉夫在宮殿底下的通道中徘徊。少了裝備，你們兩人都命喪黑暗之中。
You find yourself crawling through a twisting passage for what seems like forever.  When it comes to a dead end, you force open another panel and find yourself in the streets of Raseir.	你發現自己在一條曲折的通道中爬行，彷彿沒有盡頭。走到死路時，你強行推開另一片嵌板，發現自己來到了拉希爾的街道上。
The walls in the cell are solid, mortered stone.	牢房的牆壁是堅固的灰泥砌石。
Which one?  There are many here.	哪一個？這裡有好多個。
You already have your equipment.	你已經拿到裝備了。
You can't get to your equipment from where you are.	你目前所在的位置拿不到裝備。
The cell's door is already open.	牢房的門已經是開著的。
I'm afraid I can add but little to your knowledge.	恐怕我能告訴你的不多。
The grandmothers of our grandmothers' grandmothers were born in this place.  Katta have lived here before there was even a city. No one can keep the Katta from their home.  The Katta will come back.	我們祖母的祖母的祖母，就是在這個地方出生的。早在這座城市出現以前，卡塔族就已經住在這裡了。沒有人能把卡塔族擋在自己的家園之外。卡塔族終將歸來。
The magic of the Katta is subtle - an oil lamp that never burns out, a door that always opens to your touch, a pin that can only be seen by friends.	卡塔族的魔法是細膩微妙的——一盞永不熄滅的油燈、一扇一觸即開的門、一枚只有朋友才看得見的別針。
The new Emir is but a fool and the Underground will soon depose him.	這位新埃米爾不過是個蠢材，地下組織很快就會把他拉下台。
We are little folk, yes.  Still, we can bring down the State.	沒錯，我們是小人物。但即便如此，我們仍能扳倒整個國家。
My name, Sharaf, means "honor".	我的名字「沙拉夫」，意思是「榮譽」。
The things which you carried were placed on the table over there.	你原本攜帶的東西被放在那邊的桌上了。
Kattas understand honor in ways most humans do not appreciate.  Honor cannot be given or won by contest.  It comes to you only through diligently placing your own needs below concern for others.	卡塔族對榮譽的理解，是大多數人類無法體會的。榮譽無法被賦予，也無法靠競爭贏得。唯有持之以恆地將自己的需求置於關心他人之後，榮譽才會降臨於你。
There is little trust in Raseir, for betrayal is everywhere.  You must show me something that I know is from the Katta.	拉希爾幾乎沒有信任可言，背叛無所不在。你得讓我看到某樣我認得出、確實來自卡塔族的東西。
The sky is so bright, that it hurts your eyes.	天空亮得刺眼，讓你的雙眼感到刺痛。
Don't bother the guards.	別去招惹衛兵。
I know very little.  What is going on?  I am innocent of any wrong-doing.	我知道的不多。發生什麼事了？我沒有做錯任何事。
Waterskins under your tunic, Ugarte?  You know that smuggling water is a crime against the State.  You also know what we do to criminals like you.	烏加特，長袍底下藏著水袋？你知道走私水是危害國家的罪行，也知道我們會怎麼處置你這種罪犯。
Hero....        Help!.....	英雄……        救命！……
You are in the Plaza across from the Palace gates.	你在宮殿大門對面的廣場上。
Everywhere you look, dirty Plazas.	放眼望去，到處都是骯髒的廣場。
The UnderGround is prepared to attack the Palace.  If you need to enter there, we will provide some distraction for you.  However, we are almost ready, so you must hurry before you are caught in our battle.	地下組織已經準備好攻打宮殿了。如果你需要進去，我們可以幫你製造一些混亂來分散注意力。不過我們已經快要動手了，你得快點行動，免得被捲入我們的戰鬥。
Now through the door at the top of the stairs is Iblis.  There is some sort of spell on the door, but I don't know what it is.  There is an awful lot of magic around here.	現在樓梯頂端的那扇門後面就是伊布利斯。門上似乎被下了某種法術，但我不知道那是什麼。這附近的魔法濃度高得驚人。
The candles are being lit in the other room.  When the last candle catches fire, it will be too late.  Please, Master, stop the man from freeing Iblis.	隔壁房間的蠟燭正一根根被點燃。等最後一根蠟燭點著，就為時已晚了。拜託，大師，阻止那個人釋放伊布利斯。
